<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><title>$ command line ruby cheat sheets</title><link charset="utf-8" href="/style.css" media="screen" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" /></head><body><div class="main"><div class="header"><h1><a href="/">cheat sheets.</a></h1><code class="header">$ command line ruby cheat sheets</code></div></div><div class="content"><pre># double space a file
    $  ruby -pe 'puts' &lt; file.txt
# triple space a file
    $  ruby -pe '2.times {puts}' &lt; file.txt
# undo double-spacing (w/ and w/o whitespace in lines)
    $  ruby -lne 'BEGIN{$/=&quot;\n\n&quot;}; puts $_' &lt; file.txt
    $  ruby -ne 'BEGIN{$/=&quot;\n\n&quot;}; puts $_.chomp' &lt; file.txt
    $  ruby -e 'puts STDIN.readlines.to_s.gsub(/\n\n/, &quot;\n&quot;)' &lt; file.txt</pre></div><div class="clear"></div><div class="footer">Powered by <a href="http://www.sinatrarb.com/">Sinatra</a>,
